      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "The Kotlin compiler defines which JVM targets it can use in this source file: <a href=\"https://github.com/JetBrains/kotlin/blob/master/compiler/config.jvm/src/org/jetbrains/kotlin/config/JvmTarget.kt\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">JvmTarget.kt</a>. You can switch tags to check a specific version of Kotlin, e.g. <a href=\"https://github.com/JetBrains/kotlin/blob/v2.0.0/compiler/config.jvm/src/org/jetbrains/kotlin/config/JvmTarget.kt\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">v2.0.0</a>. In Kotlin versions up to and including 1.3.72, the file was in a <a href=\"https://github.com/JetBrains/kotlin/blob/v1.3.72/compiler/frontend.java/src/org/jetbrains/kotlin/config/JvmTarget.kt\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">different location</a>."
    } ],
